1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 Who is the Chief Minister?

The Chief Minister (CM) is:

Real executive head of the State
Leader of the government at state level
Head of Council of Ministers

📌 Equivalent to Prime Minister at state level

🔵 Appointment of Chief Minister
Appointed by the Governor
Usually leader of majority party in State Legislative Assembly

📌 In case of hung assembly → Governor uses discretion.

🔹 Council of Ministers (State)

Includes:

1️⃣ Cabinet Ministers
2️⃣ Ministers of State
3️⃣ Deputy Ministers

📌 Headed by Chief Minister

🔴 Collective Responsibility
Council of Ministers is collectively responsible to State Legislative Assembly

👉 If no-confidence motion passed → entire council resigns.

🔹 Powers of Chief Minister
1️⃣ Executive Powers
Appoints ministers
Allocates portfolios
Controls administration
2️⃣ Legislative Powers
Leader of Legislative Assembly
Advises Governor
3️⃣ Financial Powers
Key role in budget and state economy
🔹 Relationship with Governor
Governor acts on advice of CM
CM is link between Governor & Council of Ministers

📌 Similar to PM–President relation.

🔹 Important Points
CM must be member of state legislature
If not → must become within 6 months
Real power lies with CM
🔹 CM vs PM
Feature	PM	CM
Level	National	State
Appointed by	President	Governor
Responsible to	Lok Sabha	State Assembly
Role	Head of Union Govt	Head of State Govt
